Solve Barrier: I would recommend exploring food assistance programs such as SNAP (Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program) or local food banks. Gardening, even in small spaces, can provide access to fresh fruits and vegetables. 

Educate: I would educate the patient on the importance of a heart-healthy diet in managing heart failure, emphasizing the role of sodium, fat, and fiber in heart health. I would also provide information on how to read food labels to make healthier choices when shopping.